      • registerDeletionListener

        public <T extends DomainObject> void registerDeletionListener(Class<T> type,
                                                     DeletionListener<T> listener)
        Registers a new DeletionListener for the given type. The listener will be invoked whenever an object compatible with the given type (i.e. the concrete type or a sub-class) is being deleted (by calling its DeletionListener.deleting(DomainObject) method).
        Parameters:
        type - The type for which this listener will be invoked.
        listener - The listener to register.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If the DomainModel is still being assembled.

      • registerDeletionBlockerListener

        public <T extends DomainObject> void registerDeletionBlockerListener(Class<T> type,
                                                            DeletionBlockerListener<T> listener)
        Registers a new DeletionBlockerListener for the given type. The listener will be invoked whenever an object compatible with the given type (i.e. the concrete type or a sub-class) requests all its DeletionBlockers.
        Parameters:
        type - The type for which this listener will be invoked.
        listener - The listener to register.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If the DomainModel is still being assembled.
